# Heavy-runner cron entry for the 3 pheno-* substrate tools.
#
# Substituted into the user's crontab by install-cron.sh; the placeholder
# __BUNDLE_DIR__ is replaced with the absolute path of this bundle at install
# time. Do NOT edit this file in place to change the path — re-run
# install-cron.sh with the bundle in the new location.
#
# Schedule: every Monday 09:00 local time. The tools are heavy (fleet-wide
# scans across ~50 repos) and run on a self-hosted runner (device: heavy-runner
# per AGENTS.md ADR-023 device-fit gate). The MacBook is NOT a heavy-runner.
#
# Environment overrides recognised by run-with-flock.sh:
#   HEAVY_RUNNER_FLEET_ROOT  default: $HOME/code/phenotype-fleet
#   HEAVY_RUNNER_LOG_DIR     default: __BUNDLE_DIR__/logs
#   HEAVY_RUNNER_LOCK_PATH   default: /var/lock/fleet-substrate-tools.lock
#   HEAVY_RUNNER_QUIET       1 to suppress INFO lines
#
# MAILTO: local. Cron will email the user when a run produces output or a
# non-zero exit. For unattended operation, redirect to a no-op mailbox:
#   MAILTO=""
# (uncomment the line below if you want silence).
#MAILTO=""

# ┌── minute (0)
# │    ┌── hour (9 = 9 AM local)
# │    │   ┌── day-of-month (*)
# │    │   │   ┌── month (*)
# │    │   │   │   ┌── day-of-week (1 = Monday)
# │    │   │   │   │
# 0 9 * * 1 cd __BUNDLE_DIR__ && __BUNDLE_DIR__/bin/run-with-flock.sh >> __BUNDLE_DIR__/logs/cron.log 2>&1
